Acacia ataxacantha

    Authority
      Family
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 2582

   Notes
   DESCRIPTION: A scrambling shrub or climber with long slender branches,
   yellow-brown bark, with light brown slash. Flowers 4-8 cm long, dense,
   subsessile in axillary white spikes. USE: Palatable but lightly
   browsed. Much used for making impenetrable live fences. Long, straight
   shoots used as walking sticks, bows, poles. Bark used for ropes.
   Ethno-medicine against syphilis, boils, helminthiasis and wound
   treatment, headache, toothache, respiratory diseases. GROWING PERIOD:
   Perennial. COMMON NAMES: Flamethorn, Vlamdoring. FURTHER INF:
   Occasionally forming dense thickets at the Sahelian-Sudanian ecozones
   border, particularly in post-clearing successions, often associated
   with Combretum micranthum. Often located on termitaria, and
   particularly on shallow hardpans. Common along water courses with a
   favourable water supply. Found on shallow iron or lateritic hardpans,
   with a silty to loamy surface layer.

   Sources
   [10]Grassland Index
   Steven R and Staberg P 2005

